race.comment: SPEYCASTER (12) proven third-up performer who comes down from Queensland. Closed strongly from back in the field with a tidy third over 2000m at Doomben. On the quick back-up and should get the right conditions with the sharp weight drop. Genuine each way player. AGE OF SAIL (9) comes here in peak condition and doesn't have to improve much to win this. Surged late from back in the field when a sound fourth in the LR Beauford over 2300m at Newcastle. Proven at the trip and sure to be thereabouts. HOLLYWOOD HERO (10) stretches out to this trip for the first time fifth-up after catching the eye when third over 2000m in the LR Frank Underwood (ATC) Cup at Rosehill. Talented gelding who gets his chance. FUTURE HISTORY (3) gets a much better set-up for this after covering ground early before fading late when sixth over 2000m in the LR Frank Underwood Cup at Rosehill. Can take control from the draw and stays in the mix. ASTERIX (1) jumps in weight and can get the job done again. Respect.
